H.3.2.1 Overview
This sub-clause addresses the semantics of both the NoBuffer and the Overwrite stereotypes from the Activities
package of SysML. The fact that fUML does not includes foundational semantics for time prevent from describing
those for the stereotypes Rate, Discrete and Continuous. Also the way the fUML execution model is built would not
make it possible to describe the semantics of ControlOperator without an in-deep revision. The semantics of the
Optional stereotype is redundant with that of the multiplicity lower bound and so, already handled in fUML. The
semantics of Probability have no direct impact on the model execution even if it can be exploited by analysis tools.
